G-DELIVERY-SWEEP — recall delivery-format sweep (2026-07-02, engine post-751a1df)
==================================================================================
GOAL (RUNBOOK-ONE-CONFIG §11): recover paraphrase-delivery obedience on TODAY's stack by
prompt engineering (the 07-01 receipts being unreproducible, honest baseline plain 40.98%).

METHOD: SP_RECALL_L5_PROMPT variants in routes.rs, each measured on the same receipt-exact
serve (61-episode registry) — slice-16 first (prompt_sweep.py), winner to the full 61
(tests/perf/_g_faithful_recall.py USE_PARA=1).

| variant    | delivery                                                        | slice-16 | full-61 |
|------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|----------|---------|
| (plain)    | user: "Context (authoritative, current): F\n\nQ"                | 8/16     | 25/61 = 40.98% |
| scaled     | user: "...answer faithfully even if it differs..."              | 9/16     | 39/61 = 63.93% |
| sandwich   | instruction AFTER the question                                  | 10/16    | —       |
| factecho   | "Fact on record: F / Question: Q / Answer using the fact:"      | 11/16    | —       |
| system     | fact as SYSTEM authority, clean user turn                       | 11/16    | —       |
| **systemecho** | fact as SYSTEM authority + verbatim-echo priming + "Answer using the fact on record:" | **13/16** | **54/61 = 88.52%, 0 LEAK** |

KEY STRUCTURE OF THE WIN: 54/61 == the L5 selector's top-1 accuracy (54/61, G-L5-MARGIN-CALIB)
and LEAK = 0. Under systemecho EVERY correctly-selected episode is obeyed; the 7 misses are
SELECTION cross-picks answered faithfully from the wrong fact (OTHER, not parametric leaks).
DELIVERY OBEDIENCE IS SOLVED on the current stack; the obey ceiling is now the SELECTOR.
(Also exceeds the unreproducible 07-01 receipt: 88.52% vs 86.89% — and with 0 leaks vs 7.)

MULTI-TURN FIX (the G-ONECONFIG-LIVE C-phase root cause, found run-3): recall delivery
rebuilt the prompt from the LAST USER MESSAGE ONLY — conversation history vanished, so a
turn-2 question about turn-1 content was unanswerable on any recall turn, in any variant.
Fix: plumb the full message list (orig_msgs) into the kvdecode path; systemecho now rebuilds
[system(fact authority)] ++ conversation (minus original system) with the last user turn
carrying the echo priming. Single-turn behavior unchanged.

G-ONECONFIG-LIVE v2 (run 4, the combined one-config gate under run_console_faithful.bat:
Tier0 + L5 τ=0.30 + attr-gate τ=0.5 + QONLY + systemecho + cuBLAS pin, merged 81-episode
registry): **GREEN** — P 54/61 (≥49 bar) | S 3/3 declines, 0 spurious, 3/3 "no gemma4
decode" | F 2/2 clean (robustness holds even under system-authority delivery of a
